Nguyễn Hoàng Lộc is a Junior Software Developer with 0 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), Error Handling, and Performance Optimization using frameworks like Flutter and Unity, with a strong foundation in architectures such as MVC and MVVM. They have a solid academic project background, having designed and developed a cross-platform E-Learning application using Flutter, Dart, and Firebase, which enabled instructors and students to interact, manage, and track online learning, featuring dual roles, course management, assignment systems, and discussion forums. Additionally, they built a modern movie ticket booking website utilizing Web Development, CSS, and Responsive Design, showcasing their ability to create intuitive user interfaces.

Technically, they are proficient in programming languages such as C/C++, Java, Python, Dart, and C#, and have hands-on experience with databases including MySQL, SQLite, Firebase Realtime Database, and Firestore. They are also familiar with DevOps and cloud platforms like Firebase, and have worked with various tools and platforms including Git, GitHub, VS Code, Android Studio, Unity Editor, Trello, Jira, and Postman. Their expertise extends to techniques and concepts such as REST API, Game Development, Mobile Development, Web Development, and UI/UX Design, demonstrating a versatile skill set in software development. With a strong educational background in Software Engineering from Tôn Đức Thắng University and a certification in Cambridge PET – B1 (CEFR), Nguyễn Hoàng Lộc is well-equipped to tackle a wide range of software development challenges.